y and bisexual men to have large age gaps in relationships than heterosexuals or LGBTQ women. These stories reveal that queer relationships with large age gaps are not consistent with a sugar daddy/gold digger stereotype. Instead, daddies mentor younger adult men and transmit knowledge intergenerationally, including how to navigate homophobia, access gay communities, and have fulfilling sex. Silva shows that demographic research understates the commonality of age-gap pairings among gay and bisexual men, and illustrates how daddies shape gay and bisexual communities both culturally and sexually. A fascinating read, Daddies of a Different Kind breaks many commonly held stereotypes about gay and bisexual life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAging. 0aOlder gay menxAttitudes. 0aOlder gay menxSexual behavior. 0aYoung gay menxAttitudes. 0aYoung gay menxSexual behavior. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aMay December romance.  aage gaps.  aaging.  abooks on age gap romance.  adaddy.  agay and bisexual daddies.  agay.  aman-man couples.  amasculinity.  aromantic partnerships.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075163540uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479817054.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479817054423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479817054/original  a978-3-11-075163-5  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles